Collum with lateral margin weakly produced as a paranotum (
Fig. 2E
), anterior, lateral and posterior margins slightly concave, without any posterior marginal setae (
Fig. 2C
); collum dorsally bearing four transverse rows of white, short, fragile setae of nearly parallel rows.

Anterior and posterior margins of segments almost straight, with posterior marginal setae (
Fig. 2D, F–G
).

Paranota of segments set high, lying parallel to axial line and below dorsum (
Fig. 2E, H
), posterior corner of collum paranota and paranota of haplosegments 1–2 regularly rounded (
Fig. 2C–D
), that of paranota of haplosegment 3 and diplosegments until 12th produced posteriorly as broad triangles (
Fig. 2D, F–G
), that of diplosegments 13–19 strongly produced posteriorly as acute triangles (
Fig. 2L
), posterior corner of paranota of haplo- and diplosegments widely spaced from each other (
Fig. 2E, H
); anterior margin of paranota of collum, haplosegments 2–3 and diplosegments until 17th nearly regularly rounded, that of diplosegments 18–19 shallow (
Fig. 2D, F–G, L
); paranota on haplosegment 1 larger than paranota of haplosegments 2–3 (
Fig. 2D
), slightly lower than lateral margins of collum and preceding paranota (
Fig. 2E
), lying close to that of collum, but away from that of haplosegment 2 (
Fig. 2E
); lateral margins of paranota of haplosegments and diplosegments until 17th with paired weak marginal incisions, one anterior incision, one median (
Fig. 2D, F–G
); lateral margins of paranota thicker on pore-bearing rings (
Fig. 2H
).

Prozonites smooth. Metazonites, surface below paranota granulate; metazonites with moderate pubescence (
Fig. 2M
); transverse sulcus on metazonites distinct from diplosegments 1–18, reaching paranotal base (
Fig. 2F– G
); limbus a thin, continuous ribbon. Axial line clearly traceable both on pro- and metazonites until diplosegment 18th (
Fig. 2C–D, F–G
).

Pore formula normal (5, 7, 9, 10, 12, 13, 15–19); ozopore small, circular, opening posterolaterally on thickened paranotal margin, away from the level of transverse sulcus of metazonites (
Fig. 2H
).

Sterna moderately setose, as wide as long, transverse impressions more distinct than longitudinal ones, without modifications except for a single chisel-shaped, setose lamella between coxae 4 (
Fig. 2N
).

Gonopore small, round, opening on short, anterolateral mound-like bulging on coxae 2 (
Fig. 2O
).

Pre-anal ring sparsely setose; epiproct conical, flattened dorsoventrally, extending beyond anal valves, tip truncate (
Fig. 2K, M
); hypoproct triangular (
Fig. 2L
).
